<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-07-01T22:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-06-18T23:00:00-05:00" n="355" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d355">
                                <note rend="inline" type="source">
                                    <persName corresp="#p_THS1">Truman</persName> Papers</note>
                                <head>No. 355<lb/><hi rend="italic">Note by the President’s Chief of
                                        Staff</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_LFAWD1"><hi rend="italic">Leahy</hi></persName>)<note n="1" xml:id="d355fn1">Printed from the ribbon copy, which is unsigned.</note>
                                </head>
                                <opener>
                                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<date ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-sibling-dates" calendar="gregorian" notAfter="1945-07-01T23:59:59-04:00" notBefore="1945-06-19T00:00:00-04:00">Undated</date>.]</dateline>
                                </opener>
                                <p rend="center">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Flooded Lands in Holland</hi>
                                </p>
                                <p>Propose that the Reparations Commission be directed to recommend
                                    the temporary occupation by Holland of an acreage of contiguous
                                    agricultural <persName corresp="#p_LVAES1">land</persName> equal
                                    in area to the agricultural <persName corresp="#p_LVAES1">land</persName> inundated by salt water by German action
                                    during the occupation of Holland by German forces.</p>
                            </div>
                            </body></text></TEI>